			Profile
			
			XiaoLangiscurrentlyaprofessoratSchoolofEducationofZhejiangUniversity.HegraduatedfromDepartmentofHistoryofNanjingUniversityin1982.From1988to1997heattendedNagoyaUniversityinJapanandreceivedbothMasterandPh.DinEducation.In1997hereturned&nbsp;toChinaandengagedinpostdoctoralresearchintheDepartmentofEducationofHangzhouUniversityandZhejiangUniversity.HisresearchfocusesonthehistoryofChineseeducation,historyofSino-foreignculturalandeducationalexchange,historyofmodernforeigneducation.Heundertakestheresearchprojecton&ldquo;StudiesonhistoryofChinesemoderneducationalacademichistory&rdquo;,supportedbytheStateSocialSciencesFundandgotinvolvedinmanyotherimportantnationalandprovincialprojects.Hepublishedmorethan80papersinChineseandforeignacademicjournalsandoncetranslatedIntroductiontoQuantitativeMethodsforHistorians(PublishedbytheCommercialPressin1992).HeisalsothechiefeditorofInterpretationofChineseEducationalClassics(PublishedbyShanghaiEducationPublishingHousein2005),SelectedReadingsinChineseandforeignEducationalClassics(PublishedbyHighEducationPublishingHousein2009),andTheCenturyIdeal:AStudyonModernCompulsoryEducationinChina(PublishedbyZhejiangEducationPublishingHousein2000),whichwonthe&ldquo;MentionAward&rdquo;ofFifthNationalBookAwardandtheFirstPrizeof&ldquo;OutstandingAchievementsofHumanitiesandSocialSciencesofMinistryofEducationoftheThirdYear&rdquo;.HealsotookpartintheeditingofStudiesonHistoryofChineseEducation:ModernHistory(PublishedbyEastChinaNormalUniversityPressin2001),HistoryofSino-Foreigneducationalexchange(PublishedbyGuangdongEducationPublishingHousein2004),whichwonthefirstprizeof&ldquo;OutstandingAchievementsofPhilosophyandSocialsciencesofZhejiangProvinceoftheThirteenthyear&rdquo;.FromJanuarytoJune2004,hewasthevisitingprofessorofGraduateSchoolofEducation,theUniversityofTokyoinJapan.
			
				
